day 4
- overloading : methods/construtor declared with same name, but with argument list. 
- overloading happens within a single class 
- why do we need overloading 
- overloading is needed becasue instead of replacing the existing funtionalites, we just can add a new funtionality with same name but different paramenters
- overriding : the name and the parameter/arguments must be same. replacing the funtionality/ implementation of the mentod/contructor of the superclass. 
- overriding happens between a superclass and subclass
- overriding will happend if there is inheritance, or else it wont, i.e. only method will override. 
- dynamic method dispatch 
- abstraction - hiding implemtation details 
- abstract class or interface 

three layers during projects

interface
-only abstract method (only declaration)

abstractiong 
- has both abstract method and concreet method 
- partial

concreet class 
- fully completed


- interface/ abstract classes cannot have objects, but can have references
- an abstract method cannot be in a final class
- abstract and final are opposites

- exceptions - runtime errors during execution, and they terminate the program the moment exception is encountered

- object is superclass by default of java programs 
- try block must come with either finally or catch or both 
- there are two types of unchecked and checked
- to handle exception one and only option is try - catch
- ‘throws’ keyword doesnt handle the exception, it throws the error during runtime
- jvm doesnt handle the exception, it just throws the exception, 
- the actual handling is done by us
- in development
 frontend
  react, angular
 backend
   - first is controller —  controlling the flow
   - serivce layer —  data validation  , bussiness logic
   - dao/repo — database query (dao — data accept object)
   - database
- when there is an error in dao layer, it will pass the error to serive with throws, which will in turn pass it to controller, which will pass to frontend, and in frontend we use try-catch. 
- when writing code in realtime, all the functionalies must be divied into seperate files, so that they are responsible for different things. 
- throws is used to pass the error from one method to another or from one layer to another layer.
- arrays are objects in java, will take memery during runtime, from heap
 
- the classes and methods that are from version 1 of jdk, did not follow coding standards.


