- servlet :
    - java file
    - can write html code inside the file to make it dynamic web page   
    - you can create your own servlet by extending HttpServlet or GenericServelt
    - in generic servlet, you get common fucntionilty, but httpservlet gives specific fucntionalities
    - servlet life cycle 
          init( )
          service(request,response) - a generic method 
	   service can be doGet(request,response) , doPost(request,response)
          destroy( )
- jsp (java server pages) 
      - it is a html file, in which we can write java code using jsp tags to create dynamic web page
      - if the request is coming from jsp, the first it starts the translation phase
      - life cycle of jsp; jsp will translate into servlet and and then it follws the servlet life cycle??
