- session tracking — keeping the information about the user until the user logs out 
- servlet context
- there are totatl 9 inplicit object 
- out, request, response, session  — implicit objects 
- two ways of tracking the session — creating a session or a cookie 
- cookie saves the info in the client side and server is on the server side
- hence, session is secure but slow, and cookie is faster but less secure 
- in some tomcat servers, the first cookie would be the session id 
- servlet dispatcher —server side
- sendRedirecter  — client side
- dispatcher has two method — forward and include 
- forward makes a service side redirection 
- includes lets including files on server side 
